A statement in 'informaccion.es' on 16 Mar 2012
http://www.diarioinformacion.com/elche/2012/03/16/expertos-aseguran-brote-sarampion-comarca-controlado/1234481.html from the Head of Preventive Medicine at the General Hospital of Elche, Juan Francisco Navarro, said yesterday [15 Mar 2012] that the outbreak of measles recorded in the city since late January [2012] is subsiding and that it appears controlled through the preventive activities that have been developed. Since the last week of January [2012] 110 cases of measles have been registered in the region, although at present there are no patients in hospital. Specifically, the General Hospital has treated 68 cases that have resolved quickly,- Mod.CP]


