[2] UK (Cheshire/Staffordsire.
Date: Wed 14 Mar 2012
Source: (UK) This is Staffordshire [edited]
http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/Trust-confirms-measles-case/story-15516922-detail/story.html


Trust confirms measles case
------------------------
Central and Eastern Cheshire Primary Care Trust -- which covers Congleton, Crewe and Sandbach -- said it had seen one confirmed and 6 suspected cases of this potentially deadly virus [disease] in the past 2 weeks. Most of the infections are in children under 5 who had not been vaccinated at the optimum age of 13 months and babies who are too young to have the jab.

The North West Health Protection Agency has advised people with measles to avoid contact with others, particularly pregnant women, and to stay away from schools, nurseries and workplaces until at least 4 days after the onset of the rash.

