[6] Pakistan (Khyber PakhtunKhwa)
Date: Tue 13 Mar 2012
Source: WatchGeoNews, APP report [edited]
http://m.geo.tv/NewsDetail.aspx?ID=39506


Measles posing outbreak threat in parts of Khyber PakhtunKhwa
-------------------------------------------------------------
Deficiency [lack] of measles vaccine in Chitral and Malakand is posing a threat to control of the disease. The health department has declared the 2 areas as sensitive.

Deputy Director of Anti-Polio campaign Health department Dr Jan Baz Afridi said here on Monday [12 Mar 2012] that there are possibilities of outbreaks of measles in other parts of the province as well. However, children in Malakand and Chitral are the more vulnerable. He said that the health department is vaccinating children against the disease but deficiency [lack] of vaccine is creating problems. He urged the provincial government to take emergency measures and provide the vaccines so that the outbreak of the measles could be averted.

