[9] USA (Washington)
Date: Wed 4 Mar 2012
Source: Live Well, the Columbian [edited]
http://www.columbian.com/news/2012/mar/14/possible-measles-exposure-skamania-lodge/


Possible measles exposure at Skamania Lodge
-------------------------------------------
Health officials are warning people who visited Skamania Lodge last week [25 Feb - 3 Mar 2012] that they may have been exposed to measles. Skamania County health officials learned Tuesday [3 Mar 2012] that someone who had visited the lodge recently was later diagnosed with the highly contagiou disease.

The person, who was traveling internationally, attended the Open Source Technology Summit at the lodge from 6 Mar to 9 mar 2012. The person began exhibiting symptoms of measles after returning home and was diagnosed positive for measles on 11 Mar 2012.

Measles is transmitted through small particles in the air so anyone who was at the lodge or attended the summit may have been exposed, health officials said. Those who have been vaccinated against measles, have had measles in the past or were born before 1 Jan 1957 are protected against measles.

People who were exposed can receive protective antibody treatment that can decrease the risk of serious illness if given by 15 Mar 2012.

(By Marissa Harshman)

